<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
  Incentive levels in the establishment – last 12 months
</h3>
<p>
  This visual shows a monthly trend of the balance of incentive levels for the prison across the last 12 months.
  It considers the population and incentive levels averaged throughout the month.
</p>
<p>
  This average is calculated by adding all the incentives by level for each day of the month in the Ministry of Justice Analytical Platform (MoJAP) NOMIS, and then divided by the number of successful NOMIS snapshots extracted into MoJAP NOMIS.
</p>
<p>
  This is because occasionally an extract will fail.
  In the last 12 months there were 3 months that had 1 failed snapshot and the rest had none.
  This provides a very accurate average for each month.
  Even with a few snapshot failures every month, it is still a very accurate estimate of the average.
</p>
<p>
  The average monthly prison population is given in the table for additional context when looking at the absolute number of prisoners.
  It is calculated in the same way as the average prison population by incentive level, but without the incentive level breakdown.
  But this should not be relevant when looking at the bar graph, as it is looking at the proportion of all prisoners in any given month.
</p>
<p>
  This chart only considers complete months, so the current month does not appear.
</p>
